  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best free online course for website design?",
  "response": "The \"best\" free online course for website design can vary depending on your specific needs, skill level, and learning preferences. However, one highly recommended option is the \"Introduction to Web Design and Development\" course offered by the University of Michigan on Coursera.\n\nHere are some reasons why this course stands out:\n\n1. **Comprehensive Content**: The course covers essential aspects of web design, including HTML, CSS, and basic JavaScript, providing a solid foundation for beginners.\n\n2. **Practical Exercises**: It includes hands-on projects and assignments that allow you to apply what you've learned, which is crucial for mastering web design.\n\n3. **Expert Instructors**: The course is taught by experienced educators from the University of Michigan, ensuring high-quality instruction.\n\n4. **Flexible Learning**: As a self-paced course, you can complete it according to your own schedule.\n\n5. **Free Access**: While Coursera offers a paid option, you can access the course for free by selecting the \"audit\" option, although this limits your access to certain features like graded assignments and a certificate.\n\nOther notable free resources for learning website design include:\n\n- **freeCodeCamp**: Offers a comprehensive and interactive curriculum that covers web design and development.\n- **Codecademy**: Provides free courses on HTML, CSS, and other web design basics.\n- **Khan Academy**: Has a free course on basic HTML and CSS.\n\nChoosing the right course depends on your goals and the depth of knowledge you're seeking. If you're starting from scratch and want a structured learning path, the University of Michigan's course on Coursera would be an excellent choice.",
